Author: Bernz - Selling LABS#9130
Content: https://github.com/Mixa84/komodo/wiki/Pegs-CC would be a good summarization

Author: Bernz - Selling LABS#9130
Content: "It allows creating a coin that is pegged (bound) to some other currency. In essence a mechanism for creating a decentralized stable coin. Using Tokens CC and Gateways CC other crypto currencies can be deposited on chain in form of tokens and locked in an account so it can back a coin with existing value. "

Author: joe2x4#5987
Content:
```https://medium.com/@jameslee777/dual-daemon-chains-to-integrate-non-bitcoin-protocols-6d5b1b1f221
```
```Some custom code needs to be added to the non-komodo coin to implement the burn and import, but once that is done, then a 1:1 fungible dual-daemon can be created```
If Dogecoin adopted this, would this eliminate the need to atomic swap with Doge and Kmd?
```The komodo chain cluster of coda dual-daemons is thus the ultimate solution for scaling transactions. 
Make sure to only do the minimal amount of transactions on the komodo side, ie. exchange transfers and cross chain transfers to other chains in the cluster.```
Does this mean komodo is acting as gas in this instance?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: DOGE has no actual functionality other than payments, it would not make sense to do a dual daemon with it

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the dualdaemon is at the source level, and would be an independent chain, there is no DOGE protocol

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: think of dual-daemon as a way to get a totally different protocol into the ecosystem, ethereum, neo, any of the new protocols that are coming out.

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so with dual-daemon tech, we can bolt on any new protocol (even ones that are not invented yet) and make it part of the ecosystem

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: komodo is acting as the glue

Author: joe2x4#5987
Content: Seems you just created another use for kmd, Glue.

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: it works at the source level and the dualdaemon creates a new network, but in some specific cases like the codaprotocol, the result solves an otherwise unsolved problem. namely how to do 1 million tx/sec and not get flooded with terabytes of data
